-- #873 (S0, CLOSED by PR #891): a body-local ambiguous Num literal in an
-- interface-default method was grounded to Int ONLY when the impl providing
-- that default lives in the SAME module as the interface (the specialized
-- impl path, checked via inferImplMethod, whose defaultBodyLocalNum grounds
-- the var). `impl T Foo` lives HERE, in a DIFFERENT module from interface T
-- (tface.mdk), so desugar's fillImplDefaults does NOT specialize the default
-- into this impl — it is checked via the generic-default path
-- (inferDefaultMethod), which pre-#891 had no such grounding. That left the
-- element var of `s [1, 2]` (in T's default body) unbound, so `s` saw a
-- receiver of `List _a` and picked the GENERAL `impl S (List a)` (999)
-- instead of the specific `impl S (List Int)` (1) — a silent wrong VALUE with
-- `check` green either way, keyed purely on module placement.
--
-- Must print 1. A regression to 999 means the generic-default path has again
-- lost the body-local Num grounding.
import tface.{T(..), t}

data Foo = Foo

impl T Foo where
  

main = println (t Foo)
